@host = http://localhost:5214
@contentType = application/json

### Register (sets refreshToken httpOnly cookie; body returns accessToken only)
# @name register
POST {{host}}/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "correct horse battery staple",
  "displayName": "Alice"
}

### Login
# @name login
POST {{host}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "correct horse battery staple"
}

### Who am I (Bearer from login; the REST client stores the cookie automatically)
GET {{host}}/me
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

### Refresh (uses the stored httpOnly cookie; no body needed)
POST {{host}}/auth/refresh

### Logout (revokes the refresh token and clears the cookie)
POST {{host}}/auth/logout

### Logout everywhere (bumps token_version; needs a valid access token)
POST {{host}}/auth/logout-all
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}
